<% content_for :middle_bar do %>

  <div class="left-column"></div>
  <div class="right-column">
    <div class="step-arrow active" id="watching-baby"><span>Describe Your Baby</span></div>
    <div class="step-arrow active done" id="add-baby"><span>Add/Join a BabyFolio</span></div>
    <div class="step-arrow active done" id="create-acc"><span>Create Account</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="clear"></div>

<% end %>

  <div id="registration-third">
<div class="left-column">

    <div id="left-column-tooltip">
      <p><span class="bold">We're almost finished!</span> We just need to know what your baby is actually doing so we can identify the most important developments and tailor the site to your specific baby."</p>
      <div class="clear"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="right-column">
  <div id="instruction-column">
      <div id="tip-number1"></div>
      <p>Starting with the first intelligence, Language, if you've seen the behavior listed, click "I have seen this!"  If you haven't seen the behavior, click "I haven't seen this yet!"</p>
      <div id="tip-number2"></div>
      <p>If you clicked "I have seen this!" in the first step, keep going until you haven't seen a behavior and then click "I haven't see this yet!"  If you clicked "I haven't seen this yet!" keep going until you've seen a behavior and click "I have seen this!"  Follow the same process for the next intelligence.</p>
      <div id="tip-number3"></div>
      <p>When you've completed the last intelligence, click on "Finish!"</p>
  </div>
  <div id="questionnaire-column">
    <%= render :partial => 'questions_listing', :locals => {:questions => @questions, :step => @step, :categories_answered => Array.new} %>
  </div>

  <div class="clear"></div>

</div>


  
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
  $(function() {
    $('.not-seen-form').live('ajax:success', function(xhr, data){
        if(!(data.indexOf('window.location') > -1)) {
          $('.not-seen-form').parents('#all-initial-questions').replaceWith(data);
        }
    }).live('ajax:before', function(){
        $('.preloader').fadeIn();
    });
  });
</script>